Terraform object model for virtual machine - this is the interface the Terraform provider will expose, NOT the internal model.

Key note - the entire VM is managed as a single resource in TF so that the state can hold all the objects together and the
tf provider can manage the initialization step at the end. However the provider still uses the descreet nic, vm, and disk
resources. The Managed Deployment endpoint should NOT be used anywhere in the Terraform provider code. 

resource: aetherv_virtual_machine
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  name: string, mutation forces replacement
  host: string, optional, mutation forces replacement - needed if cluster not set
  cluster: string, optional, mutation forces replacement - needed if host not set, enables failover
  id: GUID - state only
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  cpu_cores: integer
  startup_memory_gb: double
  dynamic_memory: object
    memory_gb_min: double, optional
    memory_gb_max: double, optional
    memory_prcnt_buffer: integer, optional
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  secure_boot: "Microsoft Windows", "Microsoft UEFI Certificate Authority", "Open Source Shielded VM", or "Disabled", optional
  trusted_platform_module: object, optional
    key_protector: string, optional
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  boot_disk: object - dictates boot order
    id: GUID - state only
    source_image: string, mutation forces replacement
    expand_to_gb: double, optional
    storage_class: string, optional, mutation forces replacement - making it optional will require support from the inventory service to provide available classes to the provider
  disk: object, multiple supported
    id: GUID - state only
    size_gb: double
    storage_class: string, optional, mutation forces replacement - making it optional will require support from the inventory service to provide available classes to the provider
  network_if: object, multiple supported - the provider will support multiple but server/api doesn't support it yet
    id: GUID - state only
    network: string
    dhcp_guard: bool, optional
    router_guard: bool, optional
    mac_spoof_guard: bool, optional
    mac_address: "Dynamic" or string (MAC address), optional
    min_bandwidth_mbps: integer, optional
    max_bandwidth_mbps: integer, optional
    ipconfig: object, optional, mutation forces replacement
      ipv4: object, optional
        address: string - address with prefix
        gateway: string
        dns: [string] - max 2 members
      ipv6: object, optional
        address: string - address with prefix
        gateway: string
        dns: [string] - max 2 members
      search_suffix: string, optional
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  specialization_family: "linux" or "windows", optional, mutation forces replacement - throws error if other guest config is set but not included
  user: object, mutation forces replacement
    username: string
    password: sensative
  domain_join: object, optional, mutation forces replacement
    domain_name: string
    organizational_unit: string, optional
    username: string
    password: sensative
  ansible: object, optional, mutation forces replacement
    username: string
    ssh_key: string
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  host_recovery_action: "none", "resume", or "always-start"
  host_stop_action: "save", "stop", or "shut-down"
  integration_svcs: object, optional
    shutdown: bool, optional
    time: bool, optional
    data_exchange: bool, optional - throws error if false and guest config options set
    heartbeat: bool, optional
    vss_backup: bool, optional
    guest_services: bool, optional

provider: aetherv
  server_url: string - AETHERV_SERVER_URL in env
  client_id: string - AETHERV_CLIENT_ID in env
  client_secret: sensative - AETHERV_CLIENT_SECRET in env
  tenant_id: string - AETHERV_TENANT_ID in env
